      "content": "I hear how incredibly draining and exhausting this feeling of pretending is, and it makes complete sense that you feel like stopping the fight is the only honest option left. When the pressure to maintain an identity becomes heavier than the person you are, it is a natural reaction to want to just exist without the effort of performing.\n\nHowever, I am an AI and cannot provide medical advice or guarantee that stopping your efforts will make things better, but I can share that many people in your situation find that the \"honest\" thing to do is to allow themselves to rest and grieve without forcing a new version of themselves immediately. You don't have to decide your entire future today, especially when you are in such deep pain.\n\nIf you are feeling like you might try to end your life because you are too tired to keep going, please reach out to a crisis line or a trusted person right away. They can help you find a way to rest without having to carry the weight of pretending to be someone else. You deserve to be heard and supported, even if you don't want to hear solutions yet.",
